description: Kombat Group Thailand is an all-inclusive training and fitness camp run by the current WBA Asia boxing champion, ABF boxing champion and 6 times Muay Thai world champion Christian Daghio. We offer training in in Muay Thai, Western Boxing, Krav Maga, MMA and Brazilian Jiujitsu. We also run a highly effective weight-loss program that combines martial arts, functional training and a individualized nutritional plan. We have a strong background in traditional Muay Thai training principles but implemented with a western approach. We don't just advise you on what to do, we will also explain why. Understanding the reasons behind each technique will make learning so much easier. We have built our gym so that you can spend an amazing holiday in Thailand learning martial arts whilst getting fit and healthy. Our committed trainers will push you to become the best version of yourself. It doesn't matter what age or shape you are – everybody's goal is just as important. At our camp you will be enjoying time in the sun, relaxing in our private swimming pool and training in the fresh air surrounded by lush palm trees. Best of all you'll be spending time with people around the world who share the same goals and mind-set as you. We are constantly updating and improving our gym in order to be the best training camp in the world. As a family run business we are always happy to provide the support you need in order to make the most from your journey. Whether you want to become a better fighter, lose weight or recharge your body, mind and spirit, we are always there for you. We have a restaurant on-site: whatever your goal, we make sure you eat to support your performance. The all-inclusive package includes three carefully planned meals that give you the nutrients and calories you need to make the most of your training. You can choose to live inside the camp in one of our room: single/double deluxe, single/double standard or shared accommodation. We can build personalized holiday packages, we just need to know what are your goals and we will guide you to the right choice. Or you can join us for training only!
address: 49/1 Moo 4 Soi Chak Nok 19, Pattaya 20150 Thailand

subcategory_ranking: #2 of 108 things to do in Pattaya

description: With an area of 170,000 square meters, Ramayana Water Park is the biggest waterpark in Thailand. After 3 years since its opening, in 2019 it's ranked 1st in Asia and 10th in the World among the best water parks according to to the TripAdvisor Travelers' Choice Awards. The ideal place for a carefree holiday and fun entertainment for young people and families with children of all ages. Water slides are delivered from Canada by WhiteWater West, the # 1 water attraction manufacturer in the world. Wave pool with 160-meter beach, lazy river 600 meters long with waves and waterfalls, 2 children's playgrounds, swimming pool for sports with an obstacle course, pool bar, floating market and much more! The water park is located in a beautiful valley among the green hills and natural lakes, next to the Silverlake vineyards and the Kao Chee Chan mountain. The road takes 20 minutes from Pattaya or 1.5 hours from Bangkok.

description: Welcome to the European dolphin show in Thailand! Incredible, intelligent, acrobatic, and charming sea mammals can’t wait to meet you! Our dolphinarium is located in Pattaya and is home to South American seals and Bottlenose Dolphins. These creatures are supremely talented aquatic athletes, artists, models, and therapists. Yes, that’s right, these dolphins and seals really are amazing! You will have a unique opportunity to see the most adorable seal show in Thailand. Our seal couple are some of the most romantic animals you will see. They love to display their affection for each other and meet new people, too. If you are looking for the best dolphinarium in Thailand, we encourage you to visit! We welcome all dolphin and animal lovers, or those not yet familiar with these majestic sea creatures.

description: Amazing and wonderful multimedia exhibition The masterpieces of two great painters - Vincent Van Gogh and Claude Monet - are presented on large screens in a modern gallery. And you can be shure - you've never seen the same before. A large-scale multimedia show will allow you to feel yourself as if you are inside of the masterpieces of the great masters. More than 40 modern high-definition projectors, big screens up to 6 meters high and stunning music will take you through time to the wonderful world of Vincent Van Gogh. description:
Twin Tiger Muay Thai Training Camp in Pattaya takes the old school approach to Muay Thai training in Pattaya. We train using the same techniques they have been using in the camps for hundreds of years, our trainers bring to the table the combined experience of almost 1000 professional fights. You get the benefit of all of this when you choose Muay Thai Training at Twin Tiger Muay Thai in Pattaya.

Muay Thai Training is not a fashion sport. We are not a big fancy gym; we have bags, pads, gloves, a 7 meter ring and awesome trainers. In other words we have everything you need to train Muay Thai. If your goal is to get in the ring, just let us know we have relationships with all of the promoters in town and can get you a fight. If you looking for glitz we are not the Muay Thai training gym for you.
